  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.28 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-24B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+24B), dealers are currently in buy mode as spot trades above the amplifying zone. In this BREAKOUT regime with massive negative GEX (-20B), dealers will aggressively buy any dip toward 6590/6580 and sell strength into 6605/6610, creating whipsaw action in this narrow 15-point range. The gex_surge event combined with spot trading in the danger zone between these opposing gamma walls suggests we're primed for violent moves - watch for acceleration if we clear 6610 to the upside or breakdown below 6580.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings between 6590-6605 until we break out of this gamma sandwich.",
